<!--
  *** RETIRED 2026-05-13 — issue #23 follow-up. ***

  Shipping this AspirationTrack triggers an Olympus AS3 client crash at
  game launch:

      TypeError: Error #1009: Cannot access a property or method of a null
      object reference.
        at gamedata.Gameplay.shared.definitions::AspirationTrackStaticData/INIT_DATA()
        at get .../STATIC_DATA_PER_CATEGORY()
        at .../GetTrackData()
        at olympus.core::OlympusObject/ParseObject()
        at OlympusObject instance constructor()
        at HouseholdSimData instance constructor()
        ... ScenarioStaticData / NewScenariosAvailable ...

  ROOT CAUSE: when the engine serialises the AspirationTrack data row for
  AS3, one of its column reads or downstream resolutions returns null, the
  engine emits `aspirations: null` in the AS3 payload, and AS3's INIT_DATA
  crashes on `_loc4_.aspirations.length` without any guard. Once INIT_DATA
  throws, `STATIC_DATA_PER_CATEGORY` is never populated and every
  subsequent `GetTrackData(uid)` returns null — cascading to:
    - main menu shows "STR:0x..._TRIAL_NOT_TRANSLATED" placeholders
      (ScenarioStaticData constructor fails to resolve aspiration refs)
    - in-game join-career notification body renders empty (the OlympusObject
      pipeline is in a broken state for the whole AS3 client session)
    - "Job Pay" / "Time off" labels show in English even on a German
      install (same broken-pipeline symptom)

  BISECTION ESTABLISHED (this commit):
    + 4 tier aspirations (HistorianCalling_T1..T4) alone, no track  -> NO CRASH
    + this AspirationTrack alone (in any form we tried)               -> CRASH
    + uninstalling our mod entirely                                   -> NO CRASH

  So the trigger is in THIS file's SimData payload — not the tiers, not
  the career, not the Statistic, not the comment block (already stripped
  at build time), not the instance IDs (already in EA's 16-bit range).

  WHAT'S BEEN RULED OUT:
    - Instance ID magnitude: tried s=0x6621FF4B (31-bit), s=0x9ECB (16-bit,
      just past EA's max); both crash.
    - Aspiration tier IDs: tried 0x6168B380..6168B386 (31-bit) and
      0x9ECC..0x9ECF (16-bit); both crash.
    - XML comment / Unicode (the bug class that bit Statistic in #23):
      Build/s4tk-builder/build-package.mjs strips comments at load time
      regardless, so the shipped XML is bare.
    - SimData schema match: byte-equivalent to EA's Track_Knowledge_B
      (same schemaHash 0x54fdb5fc, same 9 columns, same inner-schema hash
      0xfb8c84bc for the aspirations vector). Verified by side-by-side
      column dump.

  NEXT STEPS (filed as separate GitHub issue, see commit message):
    - bisect inside this XML/SimData: strip optional fields one at a time
      (icon, primary_trait, reward, notification, provided_traits, etc.)
      and find which specific field triggers the engine-side null. The
      MAIN suspects per Docs/NOTE_cas_aspiration_picker_swf.md §10:
        (a) icon ResourceKey -> our DDS file may not resolve in the engine's
            view at the time INIT_DATA runs;
        (b) primary_trait ref to EA's 27086 may be ok but reward ref to
            EA's 27489 (Reward_Knowledge_Chronicler) may need to be a
            different EA reward type accepted by INIT_DATA's path;
        (c) the engine may require a non-empty `mood_asm_param` string
            (we emit empty, EA emits empty for Knowledge tracks — but
            other categories set it).

  Until that bisection lands, this file ships with the `_RETIRED_` prefix
  so the build excludes it. The in-game career system (the L1..L5
  CareerLevel.aspiration -> AspirationCareer chain) does NOT depend on
  this AspirationTrack — the career works without it. We just lose the
  CAS-side "Historian's Calling" pickable aspiration until this is fixed.

  ===========================================================================

  Long-form aspiration "Historian's Calling" — 4 tiers strung together.
  Showed to the player as a pick-on-creation aspiration; completing T4 grants
  the Habilitation Renown trait.

  Per EA's AspirationTrack TDESC (Build/simdata/test/fixtures/tdescs/AspirationTrack.tdesc.json)
  and the Track_Motor golden (Build/simdata/test/golden/AspirationTrack/Track_Motor.tuning.xml):

    - module is `aspirations.aspiration_tuning` (not `aspirations.aspiration_track`)
    - i is `aspiration_track`
    - the category field is a TunableReference to an AspirationCategory snippet
      (decimal instance ID), NOT an enum. Asp_Cat_Knowledge has instance ID
      25385 (0x6329) — confirmed by enumerating CombinedTuning in the live game's
      SimulationFullBuild0.package (see Build/simdata/scripts/find-aspiration-category.mjs).
    - aspirations is a TunableMapping (LEVEL_X → aspiration ref), serialised as
      a list of <U> tuples carrying `<E n="key">LEVEL_X</E>` and `<T n="value">…</T>`.
    - reward is a required TunableReference to a SimReward / AspirationReward snippet.
      We point at Reward_Knowledge_Chronicler (27489) — EA's reward for Track_Knowledge_A
      ("Renaissance Sim"). This is a stand-in until we author our own AspirationReward.
    - icon is a resource_key. We reuse Track_Knowledge_A's icon
      (2f7d0004:00000000:70f4f2b9947509f5) as a thematically-close placeholder.
    - notification is a TunableUiDialogNotification — the popup shown when the
      track completes. We use generic EA-shipped STBL keys plus our own
      HC_ASPTRACK_COMPLETE_TITLE / HC_ASPTRACK_COMPLETE_BODY.

  Reward semantics: we previously listed the Habilitation Renown trait under
  `<L n="provided_traits">`. That field IS in the TDESC (TunableSet) — these
  traits get granted while this track is the Sim's primary aspiration and
  removed when it isn't. We keep that block.

  The `aspiration_track_completion` reward chain (the trait/buff/perk awarded
  on FINAL tier completion) is a different field — `reward` (the
  AspirationReward reference at the bottom of this file). Authoring our own
  AspirationReward snippet is a v0.2 polish item.
-->
<!--
  ISSUE #23 follow-up — hand-picked 16-bit instance ID.

  Symptom: AS3 client crash `AspirationTrackStaticData/INIT_DATA() ->
  null reference on _loc4_.aspirations.length` at game launch, cascading
  to empty career notifications, English UI labels on a German install,
  and a "STR:0x..._TRIAL_NOT_TRANSLATED" placeholder on the main menu.

  Diagnosis: NOTE_cas_aspiration_picker_swf.md §5 documents this exact
  crash and suggests as hypothesis #3 that the engine's AspirationTrack /
  Aspiration native handler may not serialise our 32-bit FNV-derived
  instance IDs cleanly into the AS3 payload — producing a null `aspirations`
  field that takes down INIT_DATA() and STATIC_DATA_PER_CATEGORY with it.

  EA's actual range:
    AspirationTrack: 0x2442..0x9EC9 (9282..40649) — all 16-bit
    Aspiration:      0x23EF..0x18573 (9199..99699)

  Our previous 31-bit FNV-derived IDs (0x6621FF4B for the track,
  0x6168B380-0x6168B386 for the tiers) sit ~3 orders of magnitude above
  EA's used range. Side-by-side SimData column dump:

    EA Track_Knowledge_B (0x6361):
      aspirations[].value = 0x6368, 0x6369, 0x636A, 0x636B (16-bit)
    Our (previous, broken):
      aspirations[].value = 0x6168B383, 0x6168B380, 0x6168B381, 0x6168B386

  Fix: pin to a 5-id block in EA's 16-bit zone, just past EA's
  AspirationTrack max (0x9EC9). Verified free across all 20518 entries
  of EA's CombinedTuning by find-ids.mjs:

      0x9ECB (40651): aspiration_track_HistorianCalling
      0x9ECC (40652): aspiration_HistorianCalling_T1
      0x9ECD (40653): aspiration_HistorianCalling_T2
      0x9ECE (40654): aspiration_HistorianCalling_T3
      0x9ECF (40655): aspiration_HistorianCalling_T4

  The build's resolve-names step automatically propagates these literals
  to every cross-reference (AspirationTrack.aspirations[].value in our
  SimData, ProvidedTraits, AspirationCareer wrappers, etc.) — no other
  files need editing.
-->
<I c="AspirationTrack" i="aspiration_track" m="aspirations.aspiration_tuning" n="aspiration_track_HistorianCalling" s="40651">
  <L n="aspirations">
    <U>
      <E n="key">LEVEL_1</E>
      <T n="value">aspiration_HistorianCalling_T1</T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <E n="key">LEVEL_2</E>
      <T n="value">aspiration_HistorianCalling_T2</T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <E n="key">LEVEL_3</E>
      <T n="value">aspiration_HistorianCalling_T3</T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <E n="key">LEVEL_4</E>
      <T n="value">aspiration_HistorianCalling_T4</T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <!-- Asp_Cat_Knowledge — extracted from live game CombinedTuning. -->
  <T n="category">25385</T>
  <T n="description_text">0xTBD_STBL_KEY_HC_ASPTRACK_DESC</T>
  <T n="display_text">0xTBD_STBL_KEY_HC_ASPTRACK_NAME</T>
  <!--
    Custom icon. The build embeds Build/icons/Aspiration_HistorianCalling.png
    as a 0x2F7D0004 resource; the bare filename below is rewritten to the full
    TGI at emit time by build-package.mjs step 4.
  -->
  <T n="icon" p="HistorianCareer\Aspiration_HistorianCalling.png">Aspiration_HistorianCalling.png</T>
  <U n="notification">
    <V n="text" t="single">
      <T n="single">0xTBD_STBL_KEY_HC_ASPTRACK_COMPLETE_BODY</T>
    </V>
    <V n="title" t="enabled">
      <T n="enabled">0xTBD_STBL_KEY_HC_ASPTRACK_COMPLETE_TITLE</T>
    </V>
    <L n="ui_responses">
      <U>
        <!-- Reuse EA's "Choose New Aspiration" response text (0x7E8E7CD3). -->
        <T n="text">0x7E8E7CD3</T>
        <E n="ui_request">SHOW_ASPIRATION_SELECTOR</E>
      </U>
    </L>
    <E n="urgency">DEFAULT</E>
  </U>
  <!--
    primary_trait is the CAS personality trait associated with this aspiration
    track — shown in the Sim's trait panel while the track is active. For adult
    Knowledge-category tracks this appears to be REQUIRED for CAS visibility
    (Track_Knowledge_A/Renaissance Sim sets it to 27086; child track
    Track_Motor doesn't, but child-aspiration registration goes through a
    different code path). 27086 is the EA-shipped Knowledge category primary
    trait — borrowing it as a stand-in until we author a Historian-specific
    CAS trait.
  -->
  <T n="primary_trait">27086</T>

  <!--
    Reward trait granted while this track is the Sim's primary aspiration. -->
  <L n="provided_traits">
    <T>trait_HabilitationRenown</T>
  </L>
  <!--
    Reward chain awarded on completing the FINAL aspiration tier in this track.
    Reward_Knowledge_Chronicler (27489) is EA's "Renaissance Sim" reward —
    it grants a renaissance-themed trait/perk set. Adequate stand-in until we
    author our own AspirationReward snippet that grants e.g. a research-bonus
    perk. TODO: replace with HC-authored AspirationReward.
  -->
  <T n="reward">27489</T>
</I>
